# Jenkins — Zero to Hero

Same format as the Docker and Kubernetes guides: a staged learning path + a full command/config
reference. Jenkins is the CI/CD layer that ties everything together — it's what builds your
Spring Boot jar, builds the Docker image, pushes it, and deploys it to Kubernetes automatically
whenever you push code.

---

## Stage 0: Why Jenkins exists (30 min read)

Without CI/CD, every deploy is manual: pull code, run tests, build the jar, build the image,
push it, SSH into a server or run `kubectl apply` by hand. That's slow and error-prone.

**Jenkins** is an automation server that watches your source control (GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket)
and runs a defined **pipeline** — a sequence of steps (build, test, package, deploy) — every
time code changes. Mental model: Jenkins is the robot that does the exact same manual steps
you'd type yourself, triggered automatically, consistently, every single time.

**Where it sits in your stack so far:**
```
Code push → Jenkins → mvn build → docker build → docker push → kubectl apply/helm upgrade
```

