## Stage 2: Freestyle Jobs (Week 1) — the old way, still worth knowing

Before Pipelines existed, Jenkins jobs were configured entirely through the UI ("Freestyle
projects"). You'll still encounter these in legacy setups.

1. New Item → Freestyle project
2. Source Code Management → point to your Git repo
3. Build Triggers → e.g., "Poll SCM" or webhook-based
4. Build Steps → "Invoke top-level Maven targets" or "Execute shell"
5. Post-build Actions → archive artifacts, send notifications

**Why we move past this:** Freestyle config lives only in Jenkins' UI/database — not
version-controlled, not portable, hard to review in a PR. This is exactly why **Pipelines**
(Jenkinsfile-as-code) became the standard.

