## Stage 5: Scripted Pipeline (know it exists, Week 3)

Declarative is preferred for readability, but Scripted (raw Groovy) offers more flexibility
for complex logic:

```groovy
node {
    stage('Build') {
        sh 'mvn clean package'
    }
    stage('Test') {
        try {
            sh 'mvn test'
        } catch (e) {
            currentBuild.result = 'UNSTABLE'
        }
    }
}
```

Use Declarative by default; drop into `script { }` blocks within Declarative pipelines when
you need Groovy logic (loops, conditionals) that the declarative syntax can't express cleanly —
this hybrid approach covers 95% of real-world needs.

