## Stage 8: Building Docker Images from Jenkins (Week 5)

Two common patterns:

**Pattern A — Jenkins agent has Docker installed, shells out directly:**
```groovy
stage('Build & Push Image') {
    steps {
        sh """
          docker build -t myrepo/my-app:${env.BUILD_NUMBER} .
          docker push myrepo/my-app:${env.BUILD_NUMBER}
        """
    }
}
```

**Pattern B — Using the Docker Pipeline plugin's Groovy DSL:**
```groovy
stage('Build & Push Image') {
    steps {
        script {
            def img = docker.build("myrepo/my-app:${env.BUILD_NUMBER}")
            docker.withRegistry('https://registry.hub.docker.com', 'dockerhub-creds') {
                img.push()
                img.push('latest')
            }
        }
    }
}
```

**Project:** Extend your Spring Boot Jenkinsfile to build the multi-stage Dockerfile from
the Docker guide, tag it with `${BUILD_NUMBER}`, and push it to Docker Hub.

