## Stage 9: Jenkins Agents & Kubernetes (Week 6)

Running everything on the Jenkins controller doesn't scale. Instead, distribute builds to
**agents** — and the modern approach is spinning up ephemeral agent Pods inside a Kubernetes
cluster via the **Kubernetes plugin**.

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent {
        kubernetes {
            yaml """
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: maven
    image: maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17
    command: ['cat']
    tty: true
  - name: docker
    image: docker:24-dind
    securityContext:
      privileged: true
"""
        }
    }
    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                container('maven') {
                    sh 'mvn clean package'
                }
            }
        }
        stage('Docker Build') {
            steps {
                container('docker') {
                    sh 'docker build -t my-app:latest .'
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Each build gets a fresh, isolated Pod with exactly the tools it needs — no more "works on
one Jenkins agent but not another" drift.

