## Stage 11 (Hero): Shared Libraries & GitOps (Week 8+)

- **Shared Libraries**: extract common pipeline logic (e.g., "build and push a Docker image")
  into a reusable Groovy library that multiple Jenkinsfiles across your org can call —
  avoids copy-pasting the same 40 lines into every repo.
- Consider whether Jenkins should do the deploy step at all, or whether it should only push
  the image and let a **GitOps tool (ArgoCD/Flux)** handle deployment by watching a Git repo
  of manifests — this is the more modern pattern for Kubernetes deployments and separates
  "build" concerns from "deploy" concerns.
- **Blue Ocean** — Jenkins' visual pipeline editor/UI, useful for visualizing complex pipelines.
- **Distributed builds at scale**: pools of Kubernetes agent pods, build caching, parallel stages.

```groovy
stage('Parallel Tests') {
    parallel {
        stage('Unit Tests') { steps { sh 'mvn test' } }
        stage('Integration Tests') { steps { sh 'mvn verify -P integration' } }
    }
}
```

