## Suggested capstone project

Wire your Spring Boot + Docker + Kubernetes project (from the previous two guides) into one
automated pipeline:

1. Jenkinsfile with stages: Checkout → Unit Test → Build Jar → Build Docker Image → Push to
   Docker Hub → Deploy to your local `minikube` cluster
2. Trigger it via a GitHub webhook on every push to `main`
3. Add a manual `input` approval gate before the deploy stage (simulate a production gate)
4. Add a `post { failure { ... } }` notification step (email or a simple `echo`/Slack message)
5. (Stretch) Convert the repeated Docker build/push logic into a Jenkins Shared Library

