## How the three tools fit together

| Tool | Role |
|---|---|
| **Docker** | Packages your app into a portable image |
| **Kubernetes** | Runs, scales, and self-heals many containers across a cluster |
| **Jenkins** | Automates the pipeline that builds the image and tells Kubernetes to deploy it |

You now have the full loop: code change → Jenkins builds & tests → Docker image built &
pushed → Kubernetes rolls out the new version with zero downtime. This is the core of
modern DevOps practice — from here, deeper study branches into cloud-managed clusters
(EKS/GKE/AKS), GitOps (ArgoCD), and infrastructure-as-code (Terraform) for provisioning the
clusters themselves.
